Adviser to Japan’s Kan Urges Nuclear Waste Rethink, WSJ Reports

-- B y   J a e   H u r
-- 
2011-06-12T05:54:30Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-12/adviser-to-japan-s-kan-urges-nuclear-waste-rethink-wsj-reports.html
Japan should review its policies on
reprocessing nuclear fuel after delays in construction of
facilities and public concern about the safety of nuclear power,
the Wall Street Journal reported, citing Goshi Hosono, a top
adviser to Prime Minister  Naoto Kan .  Hosono, who has served as the prime minister’s point man on
nuclear issues, said in an interview yesterday that it’s
necessary to restore public confidence in Japan’s nuclear policy,
the report said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Jae Hur in Tokyo at 
